[{"id":41130,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">U</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>RT</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>&#947;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>6</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>U</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>R</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>T</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#947;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>7</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">U</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>RT</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#947;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>7</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>U</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#947;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>6</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>5</mn></math></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#947;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mi>f</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>7</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>p</mi></msub><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>v</mi></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>7</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (06 Sep Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41053,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["$\\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{2} \\mathrm{z}$","$\\frac{2}{\\sqrt{3}} \\mathrm{Z}$","$\\frac{3}{4} \\mathrm{Z}$","$\\frac{4}{3} \\mathrm{Z}$"],"answer":1,"solution":"Assuming mean free path constant.\n$\\begin{aligned} & \\mathrm{f} \\propto \\mathrm{V} \\propto \\sqrt{\\mathrm{T}} \\\\ & \\frac{\\mathrm{f}_1}{\\mathrm{f}_2}=\\sqrt{\\frac{\\mathrm{T}_1}{\\mathrm{~T}_2}}=\\sqrt{\\frac{300}{400}} \\\\ & \\mathrm{f}_2=\\sqrt{\\frac{4}{3}}=\\mathrm{f}_1=\\frac{2}{\\sqrt{3}} \\mathrm{Z}\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (05 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41052,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["$\\sqrt{2} \\mathrm{n} \\pi \\mathrm{d}^2$","$\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{2 n \\pi d^2}}$","$\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{2} n \\pi d^2}$","$\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{2} n^2 \\pi^2 d^2}$"],"answer":2,"solution":"$\\mathrm{n}=$ number of molecule per unit volume\n$\\mathrm{d}=$ diameter of the molecule\n$\\lambda=\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{2} \\pi \\mathrm{d}^2 \\mathrm{n}}$\n(By Theory)","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (05 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41047,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["$\\frac{7}{5}$","$\\frac{3}{5}$","$\\frac{5}{3}$","$\\frac{3}{2}$"],"answer":1,"solution":"$\\frac{\\left(\\mathrm{C}_{\\mathrm{v}}\\right)_{\\text {mono }}}{\\left(\\mathrm{C}_{\\mathrm{v}}\\right)_{\\mathrm{dia}}}=\\frac{\\frac{3}{2} \\mathrm{R}}{\\frac{5}{2} \\mathrm{R}}=\\frac{3}{5}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (08 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41085,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Molecular specific heat at constant volume in&nbsp;terms of degrees of freedom&nbsp;is given by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>V</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>f</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>R</mi></math></p><p>Molecular specific heat of mixture at constant volume is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>V</mi></msub><mo>/</mo><mi>mix</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi>C</mi><msub><mi>V</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>C</mi><msub><mi>V</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>R</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi>R</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>9</mn><mi>R</mi></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>&#945;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mi>R</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>&#945;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (29 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41138,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>15</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>13</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>20</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>11</mn></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mi>R</mi><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi>R</mi><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>15</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (02 Sep Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41094,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["A and C only","B and C only","A and B only","C and D only"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>According to kinetic theory of gases,</p><p>A. The motion of the gas molecules freezes at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math>.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>B. The mean free path decreases on increasing the number density of the molecules.</p><p>C.&nbsp;The mean free path increases on increasing the volume. Now if temperature is increased by keeping the pressure constant the volume should increase that is mean free path increases.&nbsp;</p><p>Mean free path <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#955;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mi>&#960;</mi><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>n</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>, here,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>N</mi><mi>V</mi></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>&#955;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mi>&#960;</mi><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mi>N</mi><mi>V</mi></mfrac></mstyle></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p>Using,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>N</mi><mi>K</mi><mi>T</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>&#955;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>K</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mi>&#960;</mi><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>P</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;</p><p>D.&nbsp;Average kinetic energy&nbsp;per molecule per degree of freedom is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msub><mi>k</mi><mi>B</mi></msub><mi>T</mi></math>.</p><p>Thus, B and C only.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (27 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41076,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<blockquote><p>At&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>200</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math>, the rms speed is given by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>R</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>200</mn></mrow><mi>M</mi></mfrac></msqrt><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo></math></p><p>At&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>800</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math>, the rms speed is given by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>&#39;</mo><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>R</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>800</mn></mrow><mi>M</mi></mfrac></msqrt><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>Divide equation (2) by equation (1) and solve to calculate the required speed.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable columnalign=\"right center left\" columnspacing=\"0px\"><mtr><mtd><mfrac><mrow><mi>v</mi><mo>&#39;</mo></mrow><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mfrac></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mfrac><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>R</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>800</mn></mrow><mi>M</mi></mfrac></msqrt><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>R</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>200</mn></mrow><mi>M</mi></mfrac></msqrt></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><msqrt><mfrac><mn>800</mn><mn>200</mn></mfrac></msqrt></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>&#8658;</mo></mtd><mtd><mi>v</mi><mo>&#39;</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mtd></mtr></mtable></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (06 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41037,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["-235","-253","-100","-20"],"answer":1,"solution":"The root-mean-square speed of gas molecules is: $v_{rms} = \\sqrt{\\frac{3RT}{M}}$, where $T$ is absolute temperature and $M$ is molar mass.<br><br>For oxygen at $T_1 = 47°C = 320$ K with $M_{O_2} = 32$ g/mol:<br>$v_{rms,O_2} = \\sqrt{\\frac{3R(320)}{32}}$<br><br>For hydrogen with $M_{H_2} = 2$ g/mol at temperature $T_2$:<br>$v_{rms,H_2} = \\sqrt{\\frac{3RT_2}{2}}$<br><br>Equating the RMS speeds:<br>$\\sqrt{\\frac{3R(320)}{32}} = \\sqrt{\\frac{3RT_2}{2}}$<br><br>$\\frac{320}{32} = \\frac{T_2}{2}$<br><br>$T_2 = 2 \\times 10 = 20$ K<br><br>Converting to Celsius: $t_2 = 20 - 273 = -253°C$, which is option (2).","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (21 January Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41132,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>.8</mo><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>18</mn></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>16</mn></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>16</mn></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>18</mn></msup></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>N</mi><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">V</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">T</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>U</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>K</mi><mi>T</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8756;</mo><mo>&#160;&#160;</mo><mi>N</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>P</mi><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>U</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>99</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>18</mn></msup></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (05 Sep Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41041,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"$\\begin{aligned} & \\frac{\\gamma_A}{\\gamma_B}=\\frac{\\mathrm{f}_{\\mathrm{A}}+2}{\\mathrm{f}_{\\mathrm{A}}} \\times \\frac{\\mathrm{f}_{\\mathrm{B}}}{\\mathrm{f}_{\\mathrm{B}}+2} \\\\ & =\\frac{3+2}{3} \\times \\frac{(6+2)}{(6+2)+2} \\\\ & =\\frac{5}{3} \\times \\frac{8}{10}=\\frac{40}{30} \\\\ & \\because \\frac{40}{30}=1+\\frac{1}{\\mathrm{n}} \\\\ & \\Rightarrow \\frac{40}{30}-1=\\frac{1}{\\mathrm{n}}\\end{aligned}$<br/>$\\Rightarrow \\mathrm{n}=3$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (2 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41167,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["<math><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>28</mn><mi> </mi><mi>b</mi></math>","<math><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>14</mn></mrow></mfrac><mi> </mi><mi>b</mi></math>","<math><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>b</mi></math>","<math><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>14</mn><mi>b</mi></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<math><msub><mrow><mi>C</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>p</mi></mrow></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mrow><mi>C</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>R</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow></mfrac></math> <br/><br/>For hydrogen  <math><msub><mrow><mi>C</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>p</mi></mrow></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mrow><mi>C</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>R</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi></math> <br/><br/>For nitrogen  <math><msub><mrow><mi>C</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>p</mi></mrow></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mrow><mi>C</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>R</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>28</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>b</mi></math> <br/><br/> <math><mfrac><mrow><mi>a</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>14</mn></math> <br/><br/> <math><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>14</mn><mi>b</mi></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2017 (02 Apr)","image":null},{"id":41163,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["1","3","2","<math><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<math><msub><mrow><mi>&#947;</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">mix</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">mix</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><br /><math><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>C</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>p</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>C</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>&#160;</mi><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></msub><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><br /><math><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>&#160;</mi><msub><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></math><br /><br /><math><msub><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>&#160;</mi><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>n</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>+</mo><mi>&#160;</mi><msub><mrow><mi>n</mi></mrow><mrow><mn></mn></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>n</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>+</mo><mi>&#160;</mi><msub><mrow><mi>n</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><br /><math><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"italic\"></mi><mn>4</mn><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>n</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>n</mi></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>mole</mi></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2018 (16 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":41117,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msub><mi>k</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></msub><mi>T</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><msub><mi>k</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></msub><mi>T</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msub><mi>k</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></msub><mi>T</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>k</mi><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">B</mi></msub><mi>T</mi></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Energy associated with each degree of freedom per molecule <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msub><mi>k</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></msub><mi>T</mi><mo>.</mo></math></p><p>Hence,&nbsp;the average value of energy along one degree of freedom for an ideal gas in thermal equilibrium at a temperature <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>=</mo></math><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msub><mi>k</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></msub><mi>T</mi><mo>.</mo></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (18 Mar Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41150,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["<math><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></msup><mi> </mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math>","<math><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mi> </mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math>","<math><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mi> </mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math>","<math><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></msup><mi> </mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"According to the law of conservation of energy, <br/><math><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mi>k</mi><msup><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mi>s</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mi>s</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mfenced><mo>×</mo><mi>Δ</mi><mi>T</mi></math>  <br/><math><mo>⇒</mo><mi>Δ</mi><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mn>800</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>0.5</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>400</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>4184</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>16</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>4384</mn></mrow></mfrac><mi> </mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3.65</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></msup></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (09 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41104,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>a</mi><msub><mi>P</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow><mrow><mi>e</mi><mi>R</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>","infinity","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>P</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>R</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>P</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>V</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>P</mi></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msubsup><mo>&#8747;</mo><msub><mi>P</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>P</mi></msubsup><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>P</mi></mrow><mi>P</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><msubsup><mo>&#8747;</mo><mn>0</mn><mi>v</mi></msubsup><mi>a</mi><mi>d</mi><mi>V</mi><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>ln</mi><mfrac><mi>P</mi><msub><mi>P</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>V</mi></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>P</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>V</mi></mrow></msup></math><br />Now, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></math>(as <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>)<br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>V</mi><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>P</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>V</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>R</mi><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>V</mi></mrow></mfrac></math><br />[&nbsp;for maximum <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>V</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>]<br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>P</mi><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>a</mi></mfrac></math><br />Thus, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>P</mi><mi>V</mi></mrow><mi>R</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>P</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mi>R</mi><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>P</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mrow><mi>e</mi><mi>R</mi><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (31 Aug Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41182,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["$\\frac{T_1 T_2\\left(P_1 V_1+P_2 V_2\\right)}{P_1 V_1 T_2+P_2 V_2 T_1}$","$\\frac{P_1 V_1 T_1+P_2 V_2 T_2}{P_1 V_1+P_2 V_2}$","$\\frac{P_1 V_1 T_2+P_2 V_2 T_1}{P_1 V_1+P_2 V_2}$","$\\frac{T_1 T_2\\left(P_1 V_1+P_2 V_2\\right)}{P_1 V_1 T_1+P_2 V_2 T_2}$"],"answer":0,"solution":"$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n& U=U_1+U_2 \\\\\n& T=\\frac{\\left(P_1 V_1+P_2 V_2\\right) T_1 T_2}{\\left(P_1 V_1 T_2+P_2 V_2 T_1\\right)}\n\\end{aligned}\n$$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2008","image":null},{"id":41092,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>72</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>5</mn></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>32</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>5</mn></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>27</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>4</mn></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>54</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>4</mn></msup></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>Number of moles of Hydrogen <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>m</mi><mi>M</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>16</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn></math></p><p>Number of moles of oxygen&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>128</mn><mn>32</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></math></p><p>Using ideal gas equation,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>n</mi><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></math>,</p><p>Where pressure&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>atm</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>01</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>5</mn></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>Pa</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mfenced><mi>STP</mi></mfenced></math></p><p>Putting the values,&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>01</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>5</mn></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>8</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>314</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>273</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>12</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>314</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>273</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>01</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>5</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac><msup><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></mrow><mn>3</mn></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>27</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>6</mn></msup><msup><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></mrow><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>27</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>4</mn></msup><msup><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></mrow><mn>3</mn></msup></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (29 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41160,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>5</mn></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>6</mn></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>4</mn></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>Internal energy is the energy due to thermal motion.</p><p>The internal energy of an ideal gas given by<br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>U</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>f</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>n</mi><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></math> (for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>moles</mi></math>)<br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>U</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>f</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>P</mi><mi>V</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>f</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mi>P</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mi>M</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#961;</mi></mfrac></math>&nbsp;(Since,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>&#160;</mi></math> for&nbsp;a monoatomic gas.)<br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>U</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>4</mn></msup><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>8</mn></mfrac></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>1.5</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>4</mn></msup><mi>J</mi></math><br />So, the order of energy due to thermal motion is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>4</mn></msup></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (10 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41143,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["<math><mn>1.45</mn></math>","<math><mn>1.50</mn></math>","<math><mn>1.47</mn></math>","<math><mn>1.42</mn></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"Let $n_1,n_2$ be the number of moles of gases $1$ and $2$.<br>We have $\\dfrac{C_{p_1}}{C_{v_1}}=\\dfrac{5}{3}$ and We know $C_{p_1}=C_{v_1}+R$<br>$\\therefore \\dfrac{5C_{v_1}}{3}=C_{v_1}+R,\\dfrac{2C_{v_1}}{3}R_1,C_{v_1}=\\dfrac{3R}{2}$<br>$A$ and $C_{p_1}=C_{ v_ 1 }+R=\\dfrac{5R}{2}$<br>Also, $\\dfrac{C_{ p_ 2}}{C_{ v_ 2 }}=\\dfrac{4}{3}$ and<br>$C_{p_2}=C_{v_2}+R$<br>$\\therefore \\dfrac{4C_{ v_ 2 }}{3}=C_{ v_ 2 }+R, \\dfrac{C_{ v_ 2 }}{3}=R,C_{ v_ 2 }=3R$<br>$C_{ p_ 2}=C_{ v_ 2 }+ R=4R$<br>Now $C_{ v_ {mix} }=\\dfrac{n_1C_{ v_ 1 }+n_2C_{ v_ 2 }}{n_1+n_2}=\\dfrac{2\\times \\dfrac{3R}{2}+3\\times 3R}{2+3}$<br>$=\\dfrac{3R+9R}{5}=\\dfrac{12R}{5}$<br>$C_{ p_ {mix} }=\\dfrac{n_1C_{ p_ 1 }+n_2C_{ p_ 2 }}{n_1+n_2}=\\dfrac{2\\times \\dfrac{5R}{2}+3\\times 4R}{2+3}$<br>$=\\dfrac{17R}{5}$<br>$l_{mix}=\\dfrac{C_{ p_ {mix} }}{C_{ v_ {mix} }}=\\dfrac{17}{12}=1.4166=1.42$.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (07 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41089,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math>&nbsp;and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math> only</p>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi></math> only","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math>&nbsp;and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math> only","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi></math> only"],"answer":2,"solution":"<blockquote><p>The rms velocity of a gas is given by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>V</mi><mi>rms</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow><mi>M</mi></mfrac></msqrt></math>. Therefore,<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>V</mi><mi>rms</mi></msub></math>&nbsp;is&nbsp;independent of number of moles, Hence, statement A is correct&nbsp;and D is incorrect.</p><p>According to the ideal gas equation&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>n</mi><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>P</mi><mo>&#8733;</mo><mi>n</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>P</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi>P</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>Hence, statement B is correct and C is incorrect.</p><p>Ans&nbsp;[<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#38;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math> only are correct]</p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (27 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41186,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["$3 / 2$","$23 / 15$","$35 / 23$","$4 / 3$"],"answer":0,"solution":"$\\mathrm{Q}=\\mathrm{Q}_1+\\mathrm{Q}_2$\n$\\frac{\\mathrm{n}_1+\\mathrm{n}_2}{\\gamma_{\\mathrm{m}}-1}=\\frac{\\mathrm{n}_1}{\\gamma_1-1}+\\frac{\\mathrm{n}_2}{\\gamma_2-1}$\n$\\gamma_{\\mathrm{m}}=\\frac{3}{2}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2004","image":null},{"id":41070,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>551</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>651</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>451</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>751</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<blockquote><p>The formula to calculate the rms speed of the argon molecules is given by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mrow><mi>A</mi><mi>r</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow><msub><mi>M</mi><mrow><mi>A</mi><mi>r</mi></mrow></msub></mfrac></msqrt><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>The formula to calculate the rms speed of chlorine molecule is given by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mrow><mi>C</mi><mi>l</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow><msub><mi>M</mi><mrow><mi>C</mi><mi>l</mi></mrow></msub></mfrac></msqrt><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>Divide equation (1) by equation (2) and simplify to obtain the required ratio.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>Ar</mi></msub><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>Cl</mi></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><msub><mi>M</mi><mi>Cl</mi></msub><msub><mi>M</mi><mi>Ar</mi></msub></mfrac></msqrt><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>3</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>Substitute the values of the known parameters into equation (3) and solve to calculate the required value.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable columnalign=\"right center left\" columnspacing=\"0px\"><mtr><mtd><mfrac><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>Ar</mi></msub><mrow><mn>490</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><msqrt><mfrac><mn>71</mn><mn>40</mn></mfrac></msqrt></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>&#8658;</mo></mtd><mtd><msub><mi>v</mi><mrow><mi>A</mi><mi>r</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mn>71</mn><mn>40</mn></mfrac></msqrt><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>490</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>&#8776;</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>651</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></mtd></mtr></mtable></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (12 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41035,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["$\\mathrm{O}_{2}$","$\\mathrm{NH}_{3}$","$\\mathrm{CO}_{2}$","He"],"answer":3,"solution":"For an adiabatic process ($\\Delta Q = 0$) with an ideal gas: $TV^{\\gamma-1} = \\text{constant}$<br>Given: $V_f = 8V_i$ and $T_f = \\frac{1}{4}T_i$<br>Applying the adiabatic relation:<br>$T_i V_i^{\\gamma-1} = T_f V_f^{\\gamma-1}$<br>$T_i V_i^{\\gamma-1} = \\frac{T_i}{4}(8V_i)^{\\gamma-1}$<br>$1 = \\frac{1}{4} \\cdot 8^{\\gamma-1}$<br>$4 = 8^{\\gamma-1}$<br>$2^2 = 2^{3(\\gamma-1)}$<br>$2 = 3(\\gamma-1)$<br>$\\gamma = \\frac{5}{3} = 1.67$<br>This value corresponds to a monatomic gas. Among the options, only He is monatomic ($\\gamma = 5/3$ for monatomic ideal gases). O₂ and N₂ are diatomic ($\\gamma = 7/5$), CO₂ is polyatomic ($\\gamma \\approx 1.30$), and NH₃ is polyatomic.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (22 January Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41112,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>T</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Q</mi></msub></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></msub><mo>&#60;</mo><msub><mi>T</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Q</mi></msub></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn><msub><mi>T</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Q</mi></msub></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></msub><mo>&#62;</mo><msub><mi>T</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Q</mi></msub></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>R</mi></math> for ideal gas and gas behaves as ideal gas at high temperature,&nbsp;so <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></msub><mo>&#62;</mo><msub><mi>T</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Q</mi></msub></math>.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (25 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41123,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["Statement <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi></math>&nbsp;is false but Statement <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>II</mi></math> is true.","Statement <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi></math> is true but Statement <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>II</mi></math> is false.","Both Statement <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi></math> and Statement <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>II</mi></math> are true.","Both Statement <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi></math> and Statement <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>II</mi></math> are false."],"answer":1,"solution":"The translational kinetic energy &amp; rotational kinetic energy both obey Maxwell&#39;s distribution<br />independent of each other.<br />Translational kinetic energy of diatomic molecules <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>kT</mi></math><br />Rotational kinetic energy of diatomic molecules <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>kT</mi></math><br />So statement I is true but statement II is false.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (25 Feb Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41191,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["80 K","73 K","3 K","20 K"],"answer":3,"solution":"$\\mathrm{v}_{\\mathrm{ms}} \\alpha \\sqrt{\\mathrm{T} / \\mathrm{m}} ; \\quad \\sqrt{\\frac{273+47}{32}}=\\sqrt{\\frac{T}{2}}$ or $\\mathrm{T}=20 \\mathrm{~K}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2002","image":null},{"id":41181,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["$3 \\times 10^4 \\mathrm{~J}$","$5 \\times 10^4 \\mathrm{~J}$","$6 \\times 10^4 \\mathrm{~J}$","$7 \\times 10^4 \\mathrm{~J}$"],"answer":1,"solution":"Thermal energy corresponds to internal energy\nMass $=1 \\mathrm{~kg}$\ndensity $=8 \\mathrm{~kg} / \\mathrm{m}^3$\n$\\Rightarrow$ Volume $=\\frac{\\text { mass }}{\\text { density }}=\\frac{1}{8} \\mathrm{~m}^3$\nPressure $=8 \\times 10^4 \\mathrm{~N} / \\mathrm{m}^2$\n$\\therefore$ Internal Energy $=\\frac{5}{2} \\mathrm{P} \\times \\mathrm{V}=5 \\times 10^4 \\mathrm{~J}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2009","image":null},{"id":41069,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>27</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>28</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<blockquote><p>The RMS speed is given by&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>rms</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow><mi>M</mi></mfrac></msqrt></math></p><p>The average speed is given by&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>avg</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>8</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>&#960;</mi><mi>M</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math></p><p>The ratio is&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>rms</mi></msub><msub><mi>v</mi><mtext>avg&#160;</mtext></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow><mi>M</mi></mfrac></mstyle><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>8</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>&#960;</mi><mi>M</mi></mrow></mfrac></mstyle></mfrac><mo>=</mo></msqrt><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>8</mn></mfrac></msqrt><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>8</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mn>22</mn><mn>7</mn></mfrac></msqrt><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>rms</mi></msub><msub><mi>v</mi><mtext>avg&#160;</mtext></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mn>33</mn><mn>28</mn></mfrac></msqrt></math></p><p>Comparing it with the given value&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mi>x</mi></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msup></math>,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>rms</mi></msub><msub><mi>v</mi><mtext>avg&#160;</mtext></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>28</mn></mfrac></msqrt><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>28</mn></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (13 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41042,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Kinetic Theory of Gases","question":"","options":["4205.5 J","4102.8 J","3582.7 J","3986.3 J"],"answer":1,"solution":"Kinetic energy of translation $=\\frac{3}{2} n R T$\n$\\begin{aligned}\n& n=\\frac{50 \\mathrm{~g}}{44 \\mathrm{~g}}=\\frac{25}{22} \\mathrm{~mol} \\\\\n& T=17^{\\circ} \\mathrm{C}=290 \\mathrm{~K}\n\\end{aligned}$\n$\\Rightarrow$ Kinetic energy of translation\n$\\begin{aligned}\n& =\\frac{3}{2}\\left(\\frac{25}{22}\\right)(8.3)(290) \\mathrm{J} \\\\\n& =4102.8 \\mathrm{~J}\n\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (28 Jan Shift 2)","image":null}]